Articles.Content: This mod hasnt been developed yet but i need the talents of at least one person to do it. Why? Because i have no idea how to edit the PQS on kerbin, And i need someone who can do that, essentially this mod transforms kerbin into an Asteroid, One in a cluster of asteroids all with negligible gravity, And these clusters form a belt around the sun, there will be only a few planets, Which i am considering taking from discontinued kopernicus mods with the permission of their creators, And the job of the player is to survive in this new universe, It will have a custom life support mod branched off from an existing one, And the player will have to survive.

On April 17, 2016 at 5:06 PM, daniel l. said:

This mod hasnt been developed yet but i need the talents of at least one person to do it. Why? Because i have no idea how to edit the PQS on kerbin, And i need someone who can do that

Calling @Thomas P. for you!

Interesting idea! That would definitively add a new challenge to the game if you're bored and went everywhere already. Unfortunately, I'm not very good at planet making, so I am unable to really help (I wish I knew how to use PQS mods...). However, you can use planets from the Chani pack if you think they're interesting enough for this mod.

Best of luck for this project!

Edited April 19, 2016 by Elowiny

I think a Space Engineers mod would be simpler... 

Good luck, though!

Yeah, but that's the nature of KSP - overcomplicate.

If anyone wants to test what i've got so far, Heres the download link: https://www.dropbox.com/s/9s866jnsybdaj01/KSPSE.zip?dl=0

I actually could use a little advice with a few things anyway, For example 

When Kerbin is shrunk down to 10km size the island runway intersects with the KSC how do i remove the runway? Also kerbins new terrain is entirely procedural how do i modify the scaledspace mesh or whatever to match the localspace?

 

**PAGING ADVICE** @KillAshley @Thomas P. @Sigma88
@daniel l. you can't move the island runway, but you can move the ksc to a different location (look at the KopernicusExamples on github for how to do that)
